[[logging">
== Logging
	
		You can use
		http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/Logging/article.html"> standard Java Logging]
		for logging on
		the
		App Engine. For example to define a logger in your
		class EmailServlet use the following.
	

	
		<programlisting>
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/logging/logdefine.txt[]
----
	
	
		To log a message use the following. 
		
	
		<programlisting>
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/logging/uselogger.txt[]
----
	

	

		You find your logs on the
http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/GoogleAppEngineJava/article.html#adminconsole">Admin Console]
		. the For further information see
		http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/Logging/article.html"> Java Logging Tutorial]
		and
http://code.google.com/appengine/docs/java/runtime.html#Logging"> Logging on the GAE/J]
		.
	

